Case 1:20-cr-00330-PAE Document 751 Filed 08/10/22 Page 197 of 261 1358 LC6VMAX6

1 We'll bring in the jury.
2 Counsel, was I right, those other 900 exhibits needed redaction of photos of individuals?
3 MS. MOE: Your Honor, with respect to those exhibits, just so I'm sure I understand --
4 THE COURT: 911, for example. It looks like there's a photo in the right corner.
5 MS. MOE: I just wanted to make sure we'd redacted the right thing. I received a note about that issue.
6 We weren't sure whether the issue was the painting over the mantel -- we've redacted that -- or whether there was something else.
7 THE COURT: No. On the right-hand side there's a table with a lamp. There's a lamp marked D and there's a photo of -- I can't quite tell, but I'm sure if somebody looked closely, they could tell of an individual.
8 MS. MOE: Oh, I see. Sorry, your Honor, I had not noticed that. We will unredact the painting and re-mark it to redact that photograph, if the Court requests.
9 THE COURT: Well, you tell me. Does it need to be redacted to protect privacy interests? I don't know -- for example, I don't know if this is a witness. I don't know.
10 MS. MOE: Apologies, your Honor. I'm not familiar with the person in this photograph. I can't tell from the photograph. We certainly have no objection to redacting it for

SOUTHERN DISTRICT REPORTERS, P.C. (212) 805-0300
DOJ-OGR-00012948
